{
  "title": "Patient → observation_period (derived from visits)",
  "notes": "Patient__observation_period has no FHIR field for the period bounds — they are derived in stage-2 from MIN(visit_start_date) / MAX(visit_end_date) over cdm_ours_fhir.visit_occurrence for the person (period_type_concept_id 44814724 'Period covering healthcare encounters'). This is the one cross-table edge: it reads visit_occurrence, so the case supplies the Encounters too and asserts BOTH tables. The runner runs Encounter__visit_occurrence first (PLAN order), then Patient__observation_period reads the just-produced visit_occurrence in the isolated schema.\n\nobservation_period_id == person_id == referenceToId(Patient.id) (both are hash(Patient.id)); the PK is derived and not asserted.",
